args: I'd nearly forgotten until Mary\nreminded me...
Research is fueled by raw, feral\npassion and the blind refusal to\naccept the ignominy of defeat!
These ideals form the core of who I am\nas a scientist—nay, as a human being.
I was a fool to have lost sight of that.\nNow I remember when I first seized\nhold of the dream I still cling to.
(It was back when I was just a child.\nFond of my studies, I swore I would\nbecome a researcher when I grew up.)
(As to what I'd research, well...\nI hadn't thought that far ahead.\nEven so, I devoured books voraciously.)
(I chewed through my family's entire\nlibrary end to end without finding a\nsubject that resonated with me.)
(I began to read my neighbors' books.\nI worked my way through the entire\nvillage...)

(That was when I found it, among the
personal manuscripts of a local scholar.
Her words set the gears of my fate in
motion that day.)
(Thinking back on it now, that was less an\nacademic paper and more a collection of\nthe author's daydreams on the topic.)
(I learned that creating a wormhole would\nopen up a literal world of possibilities.)
(As far-fetched as it was, reading such\nflights of fancy as a child writ them\nindelibly upon my impressionable mind.)
(More than anything, the thought of a rift\nin space-time was utterly fascinating!)
Huh? The world of...the past.\nAnd...the world of the future?!
You could just up and jump to ANY TIME\nyou wanted?! No way! That's AWESOME!
(...that someday, I would open a rift in\nspace-time with my own two hands!)
Heh. I can remember the exhilaration\nso clearly. Feels like it was only yesterday.
Imagining myself free to travel between\npast, present, and future... Even now, the\nidea gives me goosebumps.
That's it. I refuse to waste another second.\nI've got experiments to run!
A single success is worth a hundred—\nno, a THOUSAND failures. Ten thousand!
(My mind is clear again. I will not\nbe daunted, no matter the challenge!)
I've taken the perfect vacation, relishing\nin this exact moment, at this exact spot.\nI've recharged my body and mind alike.
I've reconnected with my roots—with\nthe emotional core that drives my work.
There's not a doubt in my mind.\nThis is it. THIS is what my future self\nwas talking about!
Space-time distortion field... Activate!\nI need to send this message to the past!
Control valve open! Injecting arcane slurry!\nInternal mana density has reached the\ncontrol value!
No... Mana density is spiking again?! NO!
Ugh... Another failure.\nBut I won't be deterred.
I'll try as many times as it takes!
*cough* Aha! That's the *cough* problem.\nIf I alter the timing of the slurry injection...\nNext time I'll set the control valve to...
(Hee hee. I'd almost forgotten,\nbut science is fun!)
(＂What if I did this?＂\n＂What if I changed that?＂\nIdeas flood into my mind.)
(No matter the outcome,\nthe possibilities are endless.)
Now, once more!\nSpace-time distortion field... Activate!

I'll adjust the control valve like I did in
the last round, but use the quantity of
arcane slurry I did in the round before.
Yes! I've never tried it like this!
Now, show me the money, wormhole!\nI'm on the edge of my seat here!
Yes... YES! A wormhole!\nI'VE DONE IT!
Oh no! It's destabilizing! It's going\nto collapse in on itself, and soon!
I won't let it—not before I send\nthis message. My voice can still\nreach the past.

Listen up, past Sinoa! Can you hear me?
Er, can you hear yourself? I know this
last round of failures has beaten you
down, but you can't give up!
Go indulge in a summer seaside vacation!\nThat will open the path forward to lead\nyour experiments to success!
